2020
November
I joined designer Will Chase on his stream to talk about the psycholinguistics of speech production for a data visualization project on Michael’s speech errors in The Office. Was a very cool opportunity to bring my two interests together!
October
My tutorial on stat_*() functions in {ggplot2} was featured as a highlight on the rweekly podcast, which curates weekly updates from the R community
I became a data science tutor at MindCORE to help researchers at Penn with data visualization and R programming
September
I have moved to Philly to start my PhD in Linguistics at the University of Pennsylvania!
I presented a poster at AMLaP on my undergrad thesis research with my advisors Jennifer Cole and Masaya Yoshida
June
I graduated from Northwestern University with a B.A. in Linguistics! I was also appointed as the Senior Marshal for Linguistics (but sadly missed out on the chance to carry a banner representing the major at graduation due to COVID)

